Iberdrola’s Scottish Power May Build U.K. Gas-Fired Power Plant

-- B y   B e n   F a r e y
-- 
2011-06-07T15:28:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/iberdrola-s-scottish-power-may-build-u-k-gas-fired-power-plant.html
Iberdrola SA (IBE) ’s Scottish Power may
build a gas-fired power plant near Bristol, southwest  England .  “The very first stage of consultation is set to begin this
month,” Scottish Power said today in an e-mailed statement.  The company is considering a so-called combined cycle gas
turbine station that will generate as much as 1,200 megawatts of
electricity and would be known as Avon Power Station, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Farey in London at 
 bfarey@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
